      <div class="fact-label">Traveler & Explorer</div>
    </div>
    <div class="fact-card">
      <div class="fact-num">🍜</div>
      <div class="fact-label">Food Obsessed</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="about-section">
    <h3>What I write about</h3>
    <p>My blog covers everything that makes travel real and meaningful — <strong>food & eating</strong> (street food, local restaurants, recipes from the road), <strong>trekking & adventure</strong> (trails in Bangladesh and abroad), <strong>nature & landscapes</strong> (the beautiful places that take your breath away), <strong>budget travel</strong> (how to explore more for less), and <strong>community & culture</strong> (the people who make every destination unforgettable).</p>
  </div>

  <div class="about-section">
    <h3>Why "The Unchained Girl"?</h3>
    <p>Because travel, for a woman from Bangladesh, is still an act of freedom. Every trip I take is a small rebellion against the idea that certain places, experiences, or adventures are not for us. This blog is my proof that they are. I want every Bangladeshi girl — and every woman anywhere — to see herself in these stories and think: <em>if she can, so can I.</em></p>
  </div>

  <div class="work-with-me">
    <h3>Work With Me</h3>
    <p>I'm open to collaborations with travel brands, tourism boards, restaurants, and hotels that align with my honest, budget-conscious approach to travel. Let's create something authentic together.</p>
